in a two-parameter plane. In each case, Pyragas-type feedback\nsuccessfully stabilizes the branch of small-amplitude UPOs in a neighborhood of\nthe original bifurcation point, provided that the phase angle satisfies a\ncertain restriction.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 17 Jun 2010 14:32:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-05-19"}
